According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Fidelity and Crime Insurance market was valued at USD 653 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 703 million in 2025 to USD 1,059 million by 2034, registering a CAGR of 7.8% during the forecast period. Market growth is being fueled by the increasing incidence of corporate fraud, stricter regulatory compliance requirements, and growing awareness among organizations about financial risk mitigation. Businesses across industries are increasingly investing in fidelity and crime insurance to safeguard against employee theft, cyber fraud, forgery, embezzlement, and other financial crimes. North America currently leads the market due to robust corporate governance regulations, while Asia-Pacific is emerging as the fastest-growing region driven by rapid digital transformation and expanding financial sectors.
